<SLUG> BC-GUINEAPIG-KILLING-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
MAN CHARGED WITH KILLING GUINEA PIG IN FRONT OF BOY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BHAVNA MISTRY  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   PALMDALE, Calif. -- A 37-year-old man faces felony charges of
animal cruelty and child abuse after killing a pet guinea pig in
front of his girlfriend's 7-year-old son, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   According to officials, Jesus Antonio Cruz of Palmdale grabbed
the furry rodent from the boy's arms and threw it against a wall --
twice -- during an argument with the child's mother in the
apartment they shared.
</P>
<P>
   ``The defendant picked up the pig in the child's arms and threw
it against a bedroom wall,'' Deputy District Attorney Kelly Cromer
said. ``The pig fell to the ground motionless, and the defendant
picked up the pig and threw it against the wall again.''
</P>
<P>
   Cruz had grabbed the animal after the woman told her son to get
help during the argument, Cromer said. Cromer said Cruz told the
boy, ``If you go, I will kill you.''
</P>
<P>
   Cruz and the woman had been living together for more than two
years, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   The incident occurred about 1:30 a.m. Aug. 30, officials said.
Cruz was arrested after the apartment manager called sheriff's
deputies.
</P>
<P>
   Cruz is now in custody in neighboring Riverside County, where he
was wanted on suspicion of running an illegal ``chop shop''
operation -- a place where stolen vehicles were dismantled for
parts.
</P>
<P>
   Charges were filed this week in Antelope Valley Municipal Court
accusing him of child abuse, animal cruelty and terrorist threats.
Prosecutors said Cruz faces up to six years in prison if convicted
on those charges.
</P>
<P>
   Palmdale is about 50 miles north of downtown Los Angeles.
</P>
<P>
   XXX
</P>
</TEXT>
