<HEADLINE>
INJURY SHELVING FREEDMAN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PAOLA BOIVIN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, ARIZ. - A thigh strain that has troubled Mitchell
Freedman since camp will keep him out of Saturday's game against
North Texas, Arizona State Coach Bruce Snyder said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not the opponent,'' Snyder said. ``If it was (Southern
California), we'd still keep him out.''
</P>
<P>
   Freedman's status beyond Saturday is uncertain. Snyder said the
free safety's injury worsens during competition. It also affects
his hip and groin.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's embarrassed by his play,'' Snyder said. ``We need to let
him heal.''
</P>
<P>
   The All-Pac-10 player has has been noticeably less sharp in the
two games. He has posted 11 tackles and contributed to one sack. He
had 58 tackles, two sacks and four interceptions last season.
</P>
<P>
   He has been limited to conditioning in practice this week.
</P>
<P>
   ``We need to get him in shape,'' ASU trainer Perry Edinger said.
</P>
<P>
   Junior Phillip Brown will start in place of Freedman. He has
played in both games, primarily in nickel packages, and has 10
tackles.
</P>
<P>
   Brown moved to safety from cornerback.
</P>
<P>
   The Sun Devils may catch a break against North Texas, which
prefers to run the ball. It completed only 6 of 19 passes against
Texas Tech last week. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
