<SLUG> BC-FBC-ASU-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DEVINE UNDER STANDS SNY DER'S PAIN 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By PAOLA BOIVIN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, Ariz. - If misery loves company, well,  &UR; Bruce Snyder,
move over.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Dan Devine is here to commiserate.
</P>
<P>
   Arizona State's early struggles brought back a flood of memories
for former Sun Devils coach Devine, whose 1978 Notre Dame team also
started out 0-2.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's hard to explain how lousy you feel,'' Valley resident
Devine said. ``The only way to get rid of the taste in your mouth
is with a win.''
</P>
<P>
   The Sun Devils, who have lost to Washington and Brigham Young,
will host North Texas on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   In 1978, the defending national champion Fighting Irish opened
with losses to Missouri, 3-0, and Michigan, 28-14. It got so bad
that Devine received letters demanding the benching of his senior
quarterback,  &UR; Joe Montana.
</P>
<P>
   ``Yeah, I was concerned, but what we did was come back and take
it one game at a time,'' Devine said.
</P>
<P>
   ``One at a time'' is the philosophy Snyder preaches to his
players.
</P>
<P>
   Snyder can only hope 1998 ends the way the 1978 season did for
Devine. Notre Dame won its next eight games, including five against
ranked teams. The only remaining loss was in the regular-season
finale against Southern California, which won, 27-25, in the final
seconds.
</P>
<P>
   The Irish went on to beat Houston, 35-34, in the Cotton Bowl
after trailing, 34-12, with 7:37 left.
</P>
<P>
   Can ASU expect a similar finish? Devine pointed out
similarities: high preseason expectations and a large share of new
starters.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is a horrible week for the players and coaches,'' Devine
said. ``You're just kind of waiting for Saturday night. You have to
look at North Texas as the season.'' &QL; 
Doing the shuffle &QL; 
At least six positions will have new starters against North Texas.
</P>
<P>
   Junior college transfer  &UR; Erik Flowers and  &UR; Junior Ioane will
start at end and tackle, respectively, for  &UR; Derrick Ford and  &UR; Ryan
Reilly.  &UR; Eric Fields will replace  &UR; Stephen Trejo, who is nursing a
knee sprain, at outside linebacker.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Phillip Brown steps in for free safety  &UR; Mitchell Freedman, who
has a thigh strain.
</P>
<P>
   On offense, left guard  &UR; Scott  &UR; Peters replaces  &UR; Randy Leaphart,
who is out with a knee injury. Punter  &UR; Stephen Baker will replace
 &UR; Stephen Gauthier as the kicker. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
