<SLUG> BC-FBC-ARIZONA-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IOWA'S FRY NOT READY TO CALL IT QUITS YET 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By NORM FRAUENHEIM  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Iowa Coach  &UR; Hayden Fry, a former Marine, is not in the habit of
surrendering, although there's been a not-so-subtle suggestion this
week that he consider the option.
</P>
<P>
   After his first loss to rival Iowa State in 16 years, some Iowa
fans are ready to show him the door. Or, at the very least, offer
him a retirement package.
</P>
<P>
   But, for now, Fry has no plans for a retirement home in Arizona.
A victory, maybe.
</P>
<P>
   ``No, I'd be letting my players and coaches down,'' Fry said
about sudden retirement. He's too busy this week, as his Big Ten
Hawkeyes (1-1) prepare for No. 16 Arizona on Saturday night at
Tucson. ``It's the challenge of taking something like this and
making it into a good solid, football team.''
</P>
<P>
   Trouble is, the challenge was made to sound like mission
impossible by his further comments.
</P>
<P>
   ``Tucson is not a place to look for improvement,'' said Fry, who
is in his 20th season with the Hawkeyes and 37th as a coach. ``I'm
not predicting we're going to lose, but everything sure points in
that direction. We're going to need a superb effort just to make it
competitive.''
</P>
<P>
   When told that desert temperatures continue to be at or above
100 degrees, Fry said:
</P>
<P>
   ``We're in trouble.'' &QL; 
Faster even than . . . &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Fry had an interesting scouting report on the Wildcats.
</P>
<P>
   ``Fastest ballclub we've seen in years and years, faster even
than Arizona State,'' said Fry, whose Hawkeyes lost to ASU, 17-7,
in last year's Sun Bowl. &QL; 
Still learning &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Dennis Northcutt, an ace in the Arizona air corps, was one of
the most effective players last Saturday at Stanford with five
receptions for 160 yards and a touchdown.
</P>
<P>
   But Wildcats Coach  &UR; Dick Tomey isn't satisfied. He said
Northcutt still has a lot to learn.
</P>
<P>
   ``He needs to become a better player without the ball. That's
what he has to improve on from last week.''
</P>
<P>
   Tomey cited receiver  &UR; Jeremy McDaniel as a complete player.
</P>
<P>
   ``Jeremy was everywhere with blocks and those kind of plays,''
Tomey said. ``That's what Dennis needs to do.'' &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
