<SLUG> BC-FBN-CARDS-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PLUMMER THE PUNTER? MAYBE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By STEVE SCHOENFELD  
 and TIM TYERS  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, Ariz. - If the Cardinals have to use an emergency punter,
they might turn to an all-stater from Boise (Idaho) Capital High
School.
</P>
<P>
   ``I could go out there and do it 30 yards,'' starting
quarterback  &UR; Jake
 &UR; Plummer said. ``If they put me in to pooch punt, I'd be OK.''
</P>
<P>
   Cardinals Coach  &UR; Vince Tobin asked his players after Thursday's
practice if any of them had punted before.
</P>
<P>
   Tobin was interested because punter  &UR; Scott Player suffered a
strained right-calf muscle in the workout while running down the
field in a punt return drill.
</P>
<P>
   ``I felt something pop,'' Player said.
</P>
<P>
   Tobin said he doesn't know the extent of the injury.
Special-teams coach  &UR; Al
 &UR; Everest said he hopes it's more of a cramp than anything.
</P>
<P>
   With Player's status unknown, the Cardinals likely will bring in
some punters today for a tryout. Among the available punters are
three veterans who attended a tryout with the San Francisco 49ers
earlier this week _  &UR; John
 &UR; Kidd, Greg Montgomery and  &UR; Reggie Roby. Another likely candidate is
rookie free agent  &UR; Marcus Williams, a former Arizona State punter
who was cut in training camp.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not the easiest thing in the world to do, to come right
in and punt,'' deep snapper  &UR; Trey Junkin said. '`I would think
they'd have to focus more on a veteran player who has been through
the wars. He knows what's fixing to happen.''
</P>
<P>
   Player said he thinks he will be ready to play against the
Eagles.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it will loosen up,'' he said of his right leg. ``If
not, there will be 10 guys ready to go. But I need to be out there
playing and continue to prove myself.''
</P>
<P>
   Tight end  &UR; Chris Gedney said he was asked if had punted.
</P>
<P>
   ``I haven't, but I could,'' he said. ``I know I can drop-kick
it.''
</P>
<P>
   Place-kicker  &UR; Joe Nedney probably could punt in a pinch, too.
</P>
<P>
   Although no team wants to use its starting quarterback in
punting situations, Plummer has experience and would draw
comparisons to former ASU and Dallas Cowboys quarterback and punter
 &UR; Danny White.
</P>
<P>
   ``I kicked a knuckleball in high school,'' Plummer said. &QL; 
Ready and willing &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Wide receiver  &UR; Ronnie Anderson, the former Green Bay Packer who
signed two weeks ago, is anxious to get on the field.
</P>
<P>
   He has been inactive the first two games but could play Sunday
if starter
 &UR; Rob Moore's hamstring injury isn't healed.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not here for a fashion show,'' Anderson said. ``I'm not
here to be running pass routes in practice and not getting a chance
to play. They brought me in for a reason. I worked too hard to get
where I am, not to play. I'll be ready to play; you can bet on
that.''
</P>
<P>
   Anderson thinks he knows the West Coast offense better than many
of his teammates because the Packers use it.
</P>
<P>
   ``The only difference is terminology, and once you get that
down, it's second nature,'' he said. &QL; 
Staying put &QL; 
Don't believe the talk radio speculation that offensive coordinator
 &UR; Marc &UR; Trestman, who called plays from the field the first two
games, plans to move to the press box.
</P>
<P>
   In 1989, he called plays from the field for the Cleveland
Browns, who reached the AFC championship game.
</P>
<P>
   Two years ago, he was in the press box as coordinator of the San
Francisco 49ers.
</P>
<P>
   ``Here, Vince (Tobin) thought it was pertinent for me to be on
the field to be close to Jake,'' Trestman said. '`I agree, because
there shouldn't be a buffer between Jake and I this year, and there
are adjustments to be made on the sideline. Plus, we have people
(other assistants) in the press box who can see from there what
we're doing.'' &QL; 
Short shots &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Moore and center  &UR; Aaron Graham, &UR; who has a calf injury, missed
their second consecutive day of practice. Moore said he expects to
play Sunday. Graham's status should be clarified after today's
practice.
</P>
<P>
   Linebacker  &UR; Jamir Miller, who missed Wednesday's workout because
of an ankle injury, returned to practice. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
