<P>
   &UR; A SLEEPING STORM &QL; 
 &UR; (1,700 words) &QL; 
 &UR; FOUR COLOR SLIDES &QL; 
 &UR; By CARL ZIMMER &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   Sleeping sickness _ once thought to be vanquished _ is raging
back across Africa. At the center of the epidemic, an American
doctor is trying to clear a small patch of good health. Carl
Zimmer, a senior editor of Discover magazine and the winner of the
1997 American Institute of Biological Sciences Media Award,
reports.
</P>
<P>
   SLUGGED: BC-SLEEPING-SICKNESS-NYTSF
</P>
