<P>
   ENTERTAINMENT-ARTS
</P>
<P>
   TEXAS and TEXASCHART _ Musical and variety theater in Texas.
Uses Austin Musical Theatre's recent ``Annie'' for illustration.
Musical and variety theater have led a double life in Texas, both
the most popular and the most despised types of performance. Always
associated with either frivolity or outright immorality, this kind
of theater nevertheless exists everywhere and always. Good stuff on
how Houston had two theaters before its first church. Look at
anti-musical snobbery today. (Barnes, Austin American-Statesman).
WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   NORWOOD _ Feature story on gospel singer Dorothy Norwood,
performing in Austin tonight. (Point, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   HOME&AMP;GARDEN
</P>
<P>
   FALL-COLOR _ The days are shorter, the nights cooler, and your
lawn and garden, yep, a little browner. And that's not going to
change until spring. Things don't have to look that bland. With a
little planning, your yard can have color throughout winter, and
we're not just talking pansies and rye grass. The options among
perennials, vegetables and shrubs are more plentiful than you
think. Here are some suggestions. (Flanders, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). WITH PHOTOS. ETA: 6 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-ROSH _ The Jewish High Holy days are upon us, a time
for members of the Jewish community to take a hard look at the past
year and attempt to figure out how to live their lives as better
people in the coming year. We take a look at the traditions and
rituals surrounding the eight-day period. (White, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). ETA: 6 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-NOUWEN _ He was a Catholic priest whose writings
reached across denominational and even religious lines. He was a
world-class academic who taught at such prestigious schools as
Harvard and Yale. He was courted by the rich and famous, but liked
to spend most of his time living with and helping the disabled.
Now, two years after his death, Henri Nouwen is becoming even more
popular. (Blake, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). ETA: 6 p.m.
</P>
