<P>
   The entrepreneurial spirit is alive and well, not only in the
many new start-ups spawned by the revved-up economy, but inside
corporate America. On Sept. 23, The New York Times will examine
this attitude in ENTREPRENEURS, a special news section filled with
instructive stories on ventures that worked _ and some that didn't
_ along with information useful to anyone interested in enterprise,
no matter what the scale.
</P>
<P>
   ----------------------------------------------
</P>
<P>
   A selection of these articles -- plus art -- from this section
will be made available for one-shot purchase from The New York
Times Syndicate in the next few days!
</P>
<P>
   ----------------------------------------------
</P>
<P>
   ENTREPRENEURS will explore a range of topics, everything form
the financial and management challenges facing company owners and
managers to reflections on the culture of self-employment.
</P>
<P>
   Watch the wire for more details, or call Aidan McNulty,
Associate Editor at The New York Times Syndicate, at 212-499-3338;
email mcnulaj(AT)nytimes.com. (The AT in parentheses stands for the
symbol, which can't be interpreted by newspapers' computer
systems.)
</P>
