<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-18 11:22 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A2462 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HEARST-FEATURE-BUDGET     09-18 0753
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HEARST-FEATURE-BUDGET-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EDITORS:
</HEADLINE>
  
 Friday, Sept. 18, 1998      The Hearst News Service will file the following stories for
Saturday and Sunday. If you have questions, call Tim Spence at
202-298-6920.  
    (Slugline includes the ``HNS'' tag.)
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-CALIF (Sacramento, Calif.) _ A week after independent
counsel Kenneth Starr released his report on the Monica Lewinsky
affair, Californians have lowered their opinion of President
Clinton _ but they still strongly support him and aren't ready to
eject him from office, a San Francisco Examiner poll shows. By
ROBERT SALLADAY.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-LAWYERS (San Francisco) _ Leading lawyers have this
advice for President Clinton: Make sure your lawyers don't act like
lawyers. The public is tired of hyper-technical, legalistic and
semantic arguments about the definitions of sexual relations and
perjury, they said. By SETH ROSENFELD.
</P>
<P>
   SALON-HYDE (San Francisco) _ While powerful Republicans accuse
the White House of leaking the Henry Hyde infidelity story to a San
Francisco-based on-line magazine, a World War II veteran says the
secret was first revealed through an offhand remark at a tennis
match six years ago. By MATT BEER.
</P>
<P>
   TAILWIND-SUIT (Burlingame, Calif.) _ Unappeased by the
retractions and apologies offered by Cable News Network and Time
Inc., 11 bemedaled combat veterans are suing both, charging that
reports alleging military use of nerve gas in Vietnam defamed them.
By ERIC BRAZIL.
</P>
<P>
   TREE-DEATH (San Francisco) _ An Earth First activist from Texas
has become the first fatality in the long struggle between
environmentalists and the timber industry over logging old growth
redwoods in Humboldt County. David Chain of Austin, 24, was struck
in the head and killed by a falling redwood. By ERIC BRAZIL.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   WORKING-COLUMN (Undated) _ In the era of sensitivities about
sexual harassment, it may not be easy to talk at work about the
detailed descriptions of President Clinton's extramarital affair
contained in the independent counsel's report to Congress. By L.M.
SIXEL.
</P>
<P>
   COMPUTING-COLUMN (Undated) _ The graphic report presented to
Congress by Kenneth Starr drew a lot of attention to the Internet,
but for all the wrong reasons. By DWIGHT SILVERMAN.
</P>
<P>
   HELPLINE-COLUMN (Undated) _ What is ``too much'' when it comes
to computer utilities; Is it worth it upgrading to 56K? By DWIGHT
SILVERMAN.
</P>
<P>
   CALIF-INSURANCE (San Francisco) _ Working on the premise that
the last thing most people want to do is shop for insurance,
Insurance Commissioner Chuck Quackenbush has provided a forum for
doing just that. But this is different: It's state of the art. By
GEORGE RAINE.
</P>
