   FILM-REVIEW-TRUE (Undated) _ In ``One True Thing,'' Meryl Streep
reaffirms her place in America's film acting corps: She's peerless.
No one else assumes a character as fully and selflessly, and no one
else has been as outstanding in such remarkably different roles.
Think of ``Sophie's Choice,'' ``Ironweed,'' ``Death Becomes Her.''
By WALTER ADDIEGO.
