<P>
   FINGER-BOWLS (Albany, N.Y.) _ There's nothing like a finger bowl
to lend an air of sophistication to a formal dinner table. Finger
bowls _ used for cleansing the fingers and wiping lips prior to the
dessert course _ were used at the best tables from the 19th century
through 1950. By FRANCES INGRAHAM. (For release Sunday, Sept. 20)
</P>
<P>
   TONGUE-DEPRESSORS (Troy, N.Y.) _ Dr. Alfredo B. Cruz, a family
practitioner, had too many tongue depressors. So he decided to make
use of them by building a detailed, six-foot-long model of a
Spanish sailing ship. The project also gave him something to do on
nights he couldn't sleep and it turned out to be a great stress
release. By LAURA LEE.
</P>
