DIGITAL-COMPUTERS (Los Angeles) _ Sales of DVDs are up as more
people are buying players to watch good-looking movies with great
sound. Plus, the discs contain lots of extras like director
interviews and movie trailers, and can be conveniently stored. But
DVD-ROMs _ computer-oriented titles of games _ have been slower to
come to market. By David Bloom. 
. 
FALL-TV (Los Angeles) _ Television is the lagging indicator of
popular culture. In the movies we got ``Boogie Nights'' and ``54.''
Now TV's finally jumping on the bandwagon with a mess of '70s
shows: Last year ``Love Boat'' came back; this year it's ``Fantasy
Island.'' Even a revised ``Charlie's Angels'' is in the works. By
Keith Marder. 
. 
