you listen to the networks _ each one is either the next
``Seinfeld'' or the next ``ER.'' They are all liars. This was
another in a long line of poor network television development
years. All of the inventive stuff is popping up on cable as the
networks regurgitate old themes and poorly executed plots. By Keith
Marder. 
. 
