<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of Saturday,
Aug. ??. If you have any questions, please call Kerry Schmidt on
the Star's News Desk at (816) 234-4786.
</P>
<P>
   HEASTER-COLUMN (Undated) _ Economics column by JERRY HEASTER.
Story will move in the ``f'' category.
</P>
<P>
   MORTGATE-RATES (Undated) _ The stock market turmoil has a silver
lining. As worried investors flee stocks for the safety of U.S.
government bonds, that is driving down the interest rates on bonds.
And because mortgage rates generally follow bonds, they are going
down as well. By STEVE EVERLY. Story will move in ``f'' category. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
