A3355 &Cx1f; taf-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBC-COLLEGE-REPORT-NY     09-18 0779
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-COLLEGE-REPORT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TOP GAMES OF THE WEEK 
</HEADLINE>
  (Editors: This item moves as a free-standing graphic as well) 
(JT) 
 By FRANK LITSKY    
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   No. 2 Florida 2-0
</P>
<P>
   No. 6 at Tennessee 1-0
</P>
<P>
   A slick matchup of Southeastern Conference powers. Both teams
can move the ball, although Florida lost five first-half turnovers
against Northeast Louisiana. Florida has a good defense, and
linebacker Johnny Rutledge said, ``We will throw the kitchen sink,
the wrenches, the whole house against them.''
</P>
<P>
   No. 21 Missouri 2-0
</P>
<P>
   No. 1 at Ohio State 2-0
</P>
<P>
   Ohio State rolled up 502 yards against Toledo with good passing
and Michael Wiley's 151 yards rushing. Against Kansas, Missouri
rushed for 401 yards, 319 by Devin West, but this should be much
tougher.
</P>
<P>
   No. 7 Louisiana State 1-0
</P>
<P>
   at Auburn 1-1
</P>
<P>
   Last Saturday, Auburn held Mississippi to 39 yards rushing. This
time, Auburn must contend with Kevin Faulk, who has six straight
100-yard rushing games, including 180 yards last week against
Arkansas State.
</P>
<P>
   Texas 1-1
</P>
<P>
   No. 5 Kansas State 2-0
</P>
<P>
   Kansas State has beaten Indiana State by 66-0 and Northern
Illinois by 73-7. Now it plays a major team, but even with Ricky
Williams' running (160 yards in losing to UCLA), Texas will have
trouble.
