<P>
   &UR; Late-Night TV-Talk Show as Circus Event &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Hanging On To `E.R.' &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Why We Don't Turn Off the TV &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The following articles are selections for Centerpiece package
clients this week:
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LATE-NIGHT TV-TALK SHOW AS CIRCUS EVENT &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; By JAMES TRAUB &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; FROM: The New York Times Magazine &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; For release: Sept. 20 or thereafter &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   It's the Chris Matthews phenomenon! Hard-driving political
junkie and former aide to Speaker of the House Tip O'Neill, Chris
Matthews, in cable TV's ``Hardball,'' is perfecting the art of
talk-show-as-circus. His wild gabfest devoted to Washington _ and
Monicamonicamonica _ may be the most fast and furious of all in the
genre.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; James Traub is a contributing editor to The New York Times
Magazine. (slugged: BC-HARDBALL-CENTERPIECE-$adv20-NYTSF, priority
code s, category code c) &LR;
