 &UR; By FRANK RICH &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; FROM: The New York Times Magazine &LR;  &QC; 
 &UR; For release: Sept. 20 or thereafter &LR;  &QC;
</P>
<P>
   As cable threatens network and old technology merges with new,
the medium that once brought us together is itself coming apart _
and yet television is, was and always will be the same.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; Frank Rich is a columnist for The New York Times op-ed page.
(slugged: BC-TV-CENTERPIECE-$adv20-NYTSF, priority code s, category
code c) &LR;
