<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    SEC football capsules
 &HT;    By Leo Willingham
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   VANDERBILT VS. MISSISSIPPI
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 12:30 p.m., Vanderbilt Stadium,
Nashville.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Mississippi leads 39-31-2.
</P>
<P>
   -- Records: Vanderbilt 0-2, 0-2 SEC East; Mississippi 1-1, 0-1
SEC West.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: Vanderbilt has lost its last five games to
Mississippi and 20-straight against SEC opponents. ... Vanderbilt
true freshman David Wallace started at quarterback last week
against Alabama, completing 18-of-40 passes for 167 yards in the
32-7 loss. ... Mississippi has defeated Vanderbilt the past two
years after losing to Auburn in its SEC opener. Last week, the
Rebels were shut out by Auburn 17-0.
</P>
<P>
   KENTUCKY VS. INDIANA
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 1:30 p.m., Commonwealth Stadium,
Lexington, Ky.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Indiana leads 16-11-1.
</P>
<P>
   -- Records: Kentucky 2-0, 0-0 SEC East; Indiana 1-0, 0-0 Big
Ten.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: This is the last non-conference game for
Kentucky, which has won six in a row against non-SEC opponents. The
Wildcats begin eight-straight conference games next week at
Florida. ... Kentucky has won the last three games of the series,
including a 49-7 victory at Indiana last season.... Redshirt
freshman quarterback Antwaan Randle El set an Indiana record with
467 yards of total offense in last week's 45-30 victory over
Western Michigan.
</P>
<P>
   AUBURN VS. LSU
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 5 p.m., Jordan-Hare Stadium, Auburn, Ala.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: LSU leads 17-14-1.
</P>
<P>
   -- Records: Auburn 1-1, 1-0 SEC West; LSU 1-0, 0-0 SEC West.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: Auburn begins a four-game stretch against
nationally ranked opponents _ No. 7 LSU, No. 6 Tennessee, No. 25
Mississippi State and No. 2 Florida. ... The last four games of the
series have been decided by six points or less, including Auburn's
31-28 victory in Baton Rouge last year. ... Auburn has held LSU's
Kevin Faulk to 105 total yards rushing in two previous meetings.
Faulk missed last year's game with an injury.
</P>
<P>
   ARKANSAS VS. SMU
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 7 p.m., War Memorial Stadium,
Fayetteville, Ark.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Arkansas leads 35-31-5.
</P>
<P>
   -- Records: Arkansas 1-0, 0-0 SEC West; SMU 0-2.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: Two former members of the Southwest Conference
meet for the 72nd time in a series that began in 1920. ... Arkansas
won its first game under new coach Houston Nutt last week with a
38-17 victory over Southwestern Louisiana. ... SMU is coached by
former Georgia assistant and Valdosta State coach Mike Cavan, who
has a record on 6-7 in his second season.
</P>
<P>
   OKLAHOMA ST. VS. MISSISSIPPI ST.
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 7 p.m., Lewis Field, Stillwater, Okla.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: Tied 1-1.
</P>
<P>
   -- Records: Oklahoma State 1-1; Miss. State 2-0, 1-0 SEC West.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: This is the first game between the progams in 27
years. Oklahoma State won the last meeting 26-7 in 1971. ...
Mississippi State's James Johnson, second in the SEC with 303 yards
rushing, faces an Oklahoma State defense that has allowed only
114.5 yards rushing in its two games. ... Mississippi State has
allowed only six points in two games.
</P>
<P>
   SOUTH CAROLINA VS. MARSHALL
</P>
<P>
   -- When, where: Today, 7 p.m., Williams-Brice Stadium, Columbia,
S.C.
</P>
<P>
   -- Series: First meeting.
</P>
<P>
   -- Records: Marshall 2-0; South Carolina 1-1, 0-1 SEC East.
</P>
<P>
   -- Game notes: South Carolina will be playing its third-straight
home game. The Gamecocks defeated Ball State 38-20 in their opener
and were defeated by Georgia 17-3 last week. ... Despite losing
All-American Randy Moss to the NFL, Marshall remains one of the
nation's highest-scoring teams, averaging 34.5 points in its two
victories. ... Marshall is 0-10 all-time against current SEC teams,
including a 34-31 loss to Mississippi in last year's Motor City
Bowl.
</P>
