<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR SATURDAY, SEPTEMBER 19
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Saturday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-ARCHER-DANIELS-GUILTY-NYT (moved on Thursday, September 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday,
September 17, about three former executives found guilty of price
fixing referred incorrectly in some copies to the full name of
their company and the middle initial of one defendant. It is the
Archer Daniels Midland Company, not Corporation; he is Terrance S.
Wilson, not W.
</P>
<P>
   BC-BOSNIA-ELECT-NYT (moved on Wednesday, September 16)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday,
September 16, about elections in Bosnia and Herzegovina referred
incorrectly to the office held by Alija Izetbegovic. He is one of
the three members of the country's presidency, not the president of
the Muslim-Croat Federation, a constituent part of Bosnia that is
led by a prime minister.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-SUPPLEMENT-RISK-NYT (moved on Wednesday, September 16)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday,
September 16, about the safety of nutritional supplements misstated
the outcome of a case involving a 15-year-old patient with
Hodgkin's disease who used an herbal product as treatment. The
boy's status has not been released for privacy concerns; his
doctor, Dr. Max Coppes, did not say he died.
</P>
<P>
   BC-LINCOLN-CENTER-GIFT-NYT (moved on Tuesday, September 15)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, September
15, about a $25 million gift to Lincoln Center misidentified one
unit that will benefit. It is Great Performers, which presents
classical music concerts, not ``Great Performances,'' a television
series produced by WNET. &QL;
</P>
