had stood sentinel over Holmes Flat, along the scenic route that is
part of Humboldt Redwoods State Park. Three dozen awed spectators
watched as a special team of state loggers brought down a that
officials feared would fall onto motorists along the famed Avenue
of the Giants. (Kent Porter/Santa Rosa Press-Democrat Photos) *LITE
